response.original_title: Cycling Changed My Life: Orla Walsh
response.overview: After nearly ten years partying in the clubs and bars of Dublin, fuelled by excessive alcohol and cigarettes, 31 year old Orla Walsh turned her life around to become one of Ireland's best track cyclists with multiple gold medals to her name. Orla shares the inspirational and uplifting story of her rapid transformation and GCN follows her as she competes at Ireland's National Championships in order to further her hopes and dreams of racing in the ultimate competition, the Olympics.
